inlineContent.text: In the Photos framework, collection objects (including asset collections) do not directly reference their member objects, and there are no other objects that directly reference collection objects. To retrieve the members of an asset collection, fetch them with a
. To find asset collections, use one of the methods listed in the Fetching Asset Collections group below.

Accessing or modifying the Photos library requires explicit authorization from the user. The first time you call one of the methods listed in the Fetching Asset Collections group, Photos automatically prompts the user for authorization. (Alternatively, you can use the
method to prompt the user at a time of your choosing.)

key that explains to the user why your app is requesting Photos access. Apps linked on or after iOS 10.0 will crash if this key is not present.
Like assets and collection lists, asset collections are immutable. To create, rename, or delete asset collections, or to add, remove, or rearrange members in an asset collection, create a
